# Control Flow in JavaScript

Control flow is the order in which individual statements, instructions, or function calls are executed in a program. JavaScript provides several control flow statements:

## Conditional Statements

### if...else
```javascript
if (condition) {
  // code to execute if condition is true
} else {
  // code to execute if condition is false
}
```

### switch
```javascript
switch (expression) {
  case value1:
    // code
    break;
  case value2:
    // code
    break;
  default:
    // code
}
```

## Loops

### for loop
```javascript
for (initialization; condition; increment) {
  // code to repeat
}
```

### while loop
```javascript
while (condition) {
  // code to repeat
}
```

### do...while loop
```javascript
do {
  // code to repeat
} while (condition);
```

Try the example below to practice control flow statements!

